blogs.description: A dark greenish tinge covers the sky, and black storm clouds threaten above. The wind roars loudly while cats hide under couches and dogs start howling. A tornado is forming.

comments.body: The Tri-State Tornado of 1925 holds the record for time and distance of a tornado. Named for the three states it hit—Missouri, Illinois, and Indiana—the tornado took three and a half hours to tear through 219 miles.
